title: @OspreyWTEN Travels to South Carolina Fall Classic
text: 5' 10" Jr. COLUMBIA, S.C. â€“ University of North Florida women's tennis returns to the courts with this weekend's three-day South Carolina Fall Classic. Due to the predicted rain in the forecast for the Columbia-area, the tournament's matches will take place indoors at the USC Field House Friday-Sunday. "We are excited to compete this weekend after a good two weeks of practice," said head coach . "With the UCF Tournament under our belt, we are more experience and know what to expect. We have also had some time to work on a few more detailed things in each player's game." UNC Wilmington, William & Mary, Oklahoma, Arkansas and host South Carolina join the Ospreys at the tournament. Friday's competition will consist solely of doubles matches as there are two flights with eight teams per flight. Singles play takes place on Saturday and Sunday. There are four flights of the singles competition with eight competitors in the first three flights and 12 players in the fourth flight. UNF began the fall season two weeks ago at the UCF Invite, collecting 17 total victories throughout the three-day tournament. went 3-0 in singles competition, collecting victories over Tulane, UCF and Mercer. Play each day at the South Carolina Fall Classic is scheduled to start at 9 a.m.
